==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cymene
<hw>Cy"mene</hw> <pr>(s?"m?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A colorless, liquid, combustible hydrocarbon,
<chform>CH3.C6H4.C3H7</chform>, of pleasant odor, obtained from oil of
cumin, oil of caraway, carvacrol, camphor, etc.; -- called also
<altname>paracymene</altname>, and formerly
<altname>camphogen</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cymenol</ent>⟦br⟧
